# Task Management System API

This project is a Node.js application that provides a RESTful API for a task management system. It allows users to create tasks, assign them to others, mark them as completed, and provides basic analytics on task completion.

## API Endpoints

### Create a new task
Endpoint: `POST /tasks`
Description: Creates a new task.

### Retrieve a list of all tasks
Endpoint: `GET /tasks`
Description: Retrieves a list of all tasks.

### Retrieve a single task by ID
Endpoint: `GET /tasks/:id`
Description: Retrieves a single task by its ID.

### Update an existing task (including marking as completed)
Endpoint: `PUT /tasks/:id`
Description: Updates an existing task, including marking it as completed.

### Delete a task by ID
Endpoint: `DELETE /tasks/:id`
Description: Deletes a task by its ID.

### User Registration
Endpoint: `POST /register`
Description: Registers a new user.

### User Login
Endpoint: `POST /login`
Description: Logs in a user using email and password.

### Refresh Token
Endpoint: `POST /refresh-token`
Description: Refreshes authentication tokens.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js
- Firebase Project with Authentication enabled
- Google Cloud Project with Google Sign-In API enabled

### Installation

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/Mohdhussain28/task-manager.git

# Navigate to the project directory
cd functions

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Run Server 
npm run serve

Usage
Register
To register a new user, make a POST request to /register with the user's information.

Login
To log in a user, make a POST request to /login with the username and password.

Refresh Token
To refresh authentication tokens, make a POST request to /refresh-token with the refresh token.

Dependencies
express
cors
body-parser
bcrypt
jsonwebtoken
firebase-admin

Contributing
Feel free to contribute to this project by opening issues or creating pull requests.
